subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus (
paratype
)

(
Fig. 17
). Basal piece slightly longer than wide, laterally parallel-sided, dorsally open, apically rounded; remaining parts elongate, constricted laterally just below the base of the parameres, laterally sinuous; parameres elongate, apically pointed, with triangular-shaped lateral tooth present near apices; median lobe elongate and narrow, apically pointed, deeply and narrowly bifid, slightly longer than parameres.

